comments.body:
@rhatdan @vrothberg @Luap99 @giuseppe
Gentlemens, I see that here no the sole opinion about additional providers as part of podman. I also understand, that adding and supporting a redundant stack will lead to an extra cost and might complicate all. In this regard, I want to know your opinions about allowing users to use their own or/and extra providers which are not a part of podman, with some command-line options in podman machine, for instance, it could be in the next way or similar - `podman machine init --extra-provider=/path/to/a/binary/provider/file`
So, what do you think about this suggestion? If this is supported from your side, I'll continue to work on including described approach support within the current PR and VBox provider will be brought out of podman.
